<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="AppDiffEVT" checkit-title="Extreme Value Theorem">
    <statement>
        <p> 
Explain how to find the absolute minimum and absolute maximum values of the
function <m>f(x)=-2 \, x^{3} + 18 \, x^{2} + 42 \, x - 46</m> on the interval <m>[-4,2]</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
The absolute extrema may occur at these <m>x</m>-values:
<m>-4, -1, 2</m>.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><p><m>f(-4)=202</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(-1)=-68</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(2)=94</m></p></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
Thus the absolute minimum is <m>-68</m> and the absolute
maximum is <m>202</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
(The value <m>f(7)=444</m>
is ignored as <m>7</m> isn't in the given interval.)
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
